    "answer_id" : 44644764,
    "question_id" : 44644434,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>There is no <code>javax.servlet-api.jar</code> in the classpath. Maybe it is not in tomcat's lib folder.\n Try to add this jar to your <code>WEB-INF/lib</code> directory. To download a jar go to <a href=\"https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/javax.servlet/javax.servlet-api/3.1.0\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/javax.servlet/javax.servlet-api/3.1.0</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 23944708,
      "reputation" : 47,
      "user_id" : 17937223,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/055560a3189809e847795097d22eb71a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "catloverxx",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/17937223/catloverxx"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : -2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1668916185,
    "last_edit_date" : 1668916185,
    "creation_date" : 1654633221,
    "answer_id" : 72537135,
    "question_id" : 44644434,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I had the same problem when I first tried to use Tomcat. If you imported <code>HttpServlet</code> class from <code>jakarta.servlet.http</code> try importing it from <code>javax.servlet.http</code> instead, that's what worked for me. <br>Since I used <code>jakarta-servlet-api</code> dependency I expected to find the <code>HttpServlet</code> class in the <code>javax.servlet.http</code> package, however I was wrong. <br>\nI extracted the <code>jakarta-servlet-api.jar</code> and saw that the package is called javax. <br>\nSo I imported HttpServlet from <code>javax.servlet.http</code> instead and it worked fine.</p>\n"
  }, {
